definitions.definition: sharp, hard extensions of the cortex and epidermis of some plants (such as roses ), informally called " thorns " in colloquial speech .
A small, sharp pointed object similar to the true prickle, such as a thorn .
A tingling sensation of mild discomfort .
A sieve of hazelnuts , weighing about fifty pounds .
A group of hedgehogs or porcupines .

main_definition: ( botany ) sharp, hard extensions of the cortex and epidermis of some plants (such as roses ), informally called " thorns " in colloquial speech .
secondary_definitions: A small, sharp pointed object similar to the true prickle, such as a thorn .
A tingling sensation of mild discomfort .
( UK , obsolete ) A sieve of hazelnuts , weighing about fifty pounds .
( collective ) A group of hedgehogs or porcupines .
